<exercise checkit-seed="0001" checkit-slug="P5" checkit-title="Expected Value">
    <statement>
                <p> Tao is gambling at a roullette wheel. The wheel has 21 equally sized spots. 8 of the spots are winning locations, and the rest are losing. If costs \$5 to play the wheel. If Tao wins, they get their bet back and they win \$16, otherwise they forfeit their bet. What is the expected value of this gamble?
                </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            The expected value is <m>\frac{8}{21}(16) + \frac{13}{21}(-5) = $2.99</m>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
